CONFIGURATIONS

PEERS:
$ java Peer <protocol_version> <peer_id> <peer_ap> <mc_address> <mc_port> <mdb_address> <mdb_port> <mdr_address> <mdr_port>

PEER_1 -> 1.0 1 1099 230.0.0.1 8081 230.0.0.2 8082 230.0.0.3 8083
PEER_2 -> 1.0 2 2099 230.0.0.1 8081 230.0.0.2 8082 230.0.0.3 8083
PEER_3 -> 1.0 3 3099 230.0.0.1 8081 230.0.0.2 8082 230.0.0.3 8083

CLIENT (TestApp):
$ java TestApp <peer_ap> <sub_protocol> <opnd_1> <opnd_2>
$ java TestApp 1923 BACKUP test1.pdf 3 
$ java TestApp 1923 RESTORE test1.pdf
$ java TestApp 1923 DELETE test1.pdf
$ java TestApp 1923 RECLAIM 0
$ java TestApp 1923 STATE


